Suitably horrible trade-off, given how useful this thing would be otherwise. I do have to wonder about all the screaming, though it's fine that 842 is keeping the subjects alive through a procedure that would otherwise kill them, but screaming involves use of the lungs, which would presumably be outside the subject's control (along with the rest of their organs) after they become 842-1.

That 842 would allow its subjects to vocalize despite needing their mouths as a  amnesia mishap stories you hear about from time to time. Not a huge issue, though- it's still getting my upvote.







